For years, scientists have been confused by a mysterious phenomenon called swing-by anomaly.
Swing-by is the gravitational rocking machine of space probes, which generates additional momentum in the gravitational space of a celestial body, such as the Earth.
So the probes can save a large amount of fuel.
The European-American Cassini-Huygens research probe, like Ulysses Sun probe, used this physical trick.
However, what amazes researchers for many years: Flying objects do not behave fully as would be expected under the ancient Gravity Act.
Instead, there are anomalies in speed.
The probes are unexpectedly accelerating or slowing down.
