If the phenomenon is very intense, it is recommended to observe the child and consult a specialist. The examination may reveal whether there is a major anxiety problem behind it and thus offer a solution.
As mentioned above, this is a benign phenomenon and therefore there is no cure unless it is accompanied by another treatable form of sleep disorder (e.g. insomnia or stress).
