The legislation allows the companies concerned to participate in an insurance scheme where the financial portfolio guarantees the assets of concern for which companies will pay a fee corresponding to the expected damage.
Henry Paulson said that the law provides the necessary means to reach the urgent needs of the US financial system, up to $700 billion, whether it is a widespread purchase of bad assets, whether they are insured or the risk of systemic collapse of a large financial institution.
We are taking the necessary steps to be ready to introduce the law as soon as it is signed, he added.
